        <p class="pageHeading">Absence Policy </p>
<p class="categoryHeading">It is a mandatory requirement to follow this procedure.</p>     
 
<p>NCS is required to notify the Staffing Unit of all absentee items when someone is absent from a scheduled time of work.  This includes (but is not limited to), vacations, illness, doctor's appointments, dental appointments, weddings, funerals, personal time, etc.  </p>
 
<p>In addition to notifying your contact person of your absence, also send an email to each of the email addresses below.  When an illness requires an extended time away from work, our receiving status updates of recovery is imperative and we need your contact information.   Although email notification is preferred, if you do not have access to email, you may call one of the numbers listed below.  Notification of absence should include reason for absence and duration (if known).  Again, this procedure does not replace the requirement of your notifying your contact person of your absence from work.</p>
